    <header class="article-header">
      <p class="article-meta">Published March 29, 2026</p>
      <h1>How Much Does College Really Cost in 2026?</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">The sticker price of a college education continues to climb, but the number on the brochure rarely tells the full story. Between published tuition rates, net prices after financial aid, hidden fees, and living expenses, understanding what college actually costs requires looking beyond the headline figures. This guide breaks down the true cost of attending college in 2026 by institution type, examines how tuition has trended over the past decade, identifies the hidden expenses families often overlook, and explores the return on investment a degree provides — along with practical strategies to reduce what you pay.</p>
    </header>

    <AdUnit slot="blog-top" format="horizontal" />

